  "notes": [
    "Kenya registration plates follow the format KXX 000X (3-letter prefix, space, 3 digits, 1 letter suffix).",
    "The letter 'I' and 'O' are omitted from prefixes to avoid confusion with numbers 1 and 0.",
    "Registration is centralized in Nairobi — the prefix does NOT indicate where the vehicle operates, only where it was registered.",
    "Since 2004, nearly all new registrations are processed in Nairobi, making prefix-to-county mapping less meaningful for newer plates."
